d States Government customers and national security applications.\n    *   **Satellite Manufacturing:** The segment leverages a highly integrated satellite platform spanning architecture, chip design, software, power systems, and final assembly. This allows the company to design, engineer, and manufacture advanced satellites at scale, incorporating over 23,000 inter-satellite lasers to create a dynamic mesh network in space.\n\n**3. AI Segment**\n*   **Products & Services:** Operates a highly vertically integrated AI platform spanning gigawatt-scale AI compute infrastructure, frontier AI models, AI solutions for consumer and enterprise customers, and a real-time information platform.\n*   **Key Activities & Offerings:**\n    *   **xAI & Grok:** xAI (acquired by SpaceX in early 2026) operates the truth-seeking frontier Large Language Model (LLM) known as Grok, which is used for AI solutions across consumer and enterprise customers.\n    *   **X Platform:** Includes X, a real-time information, entertainment, and free speech platform.\n    *   **Terrestrial AI Compute Infrastructure:** Owns and operates what it believes to be the largest AI training data center clusters on Earth, including COLOSSUS and COLOSSUS II. It was the first company to deploy a coherent gigawatt-scale AI training cluster. It is also developing "Terafab," a chip manufacturing initiative with Tesla and Intel.\n    *   **Orbital AI Compute Activities:** Plans to deploy orbital AI compute satellites as early as 2028. These satellites in Sun-synchronous orbit are expected to handle energy-intensive AI workloads, such as inference demand, at far greater scale and efficiency than terrestrial alternatives, using Starlink for low-latency, global connectivity.',
