    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Segment Measurement, Profitability, and Cost Allocation\n\n## How Segment Results Are Measured and Reported\n\nBased on the disclosures, segment results are measured and reported as follows:\n\n**Reporting Structure:** Following the Mergers, effective Q1 2026, the CEO (as CODM) organizes the Company into three operating and reportable segments—Space, Connectivity, and AI. Prior period presentations were conformed to this structure.\n\n**Measurement Basis:** The CODM assesses performance and allocates resources based on **segment income (loss) from operations**, by comparing actual results to historical results and previously forecasted financial information. The disclosed tables present revenues, significant segment expenses (cost of revenue, R&D, SG&A, restructuring, impairment), and income (loss) from operations for each segment.\n\n## Segment Profitability Measure\n\nThe primary GAAP profitability measure is **Income (Loss) from Operations** at the segment level. The Company also reports a non-GAAP measure—**Segment Adjusted EBITDA**—reconciled from income (loss) from operations by adding back depreciation and amortization, share-based compensation, restructuring charges, and impairment.\n\n## Shared Costs and Corporate Overhead Allocation\n\nThe disclosures are **limited** on allocation methodology. The only specific reference found states that the Space segment\'s SG&A expenses include **"allocated employee compensation costs"** (salaries, benefits, share-based compensation) for sales, facilities, legal, finance, IT, HR, and other administrative employees, plus depreciation and corporate aircraft costs. However, **no allocation methodology or basis** (e.g., headcount, revenue, usage) is disclosed.\n\n## Inter-Segment Cost Transfers\n\n**No disclosures** were found in the provided chunks regarding:\n- The methodology for allocating shared/corporate overhead across segments\n- Inter-segment cost transfers or transfer pricing between Space, Connectivity, and AI\n- How shared infrastructure (e.g., launch facilities used by both Space and Connectivity) is cost-shared\n\nThe text notes the CODM "does not evaluate operating and reportable segments using" additional measures, but the sentence is truncated before completing this thought.',
